HTML::WikiConverter::Kwiki version 0.51
=======================================

HTML::WikiConverter::Kwiki adds the Kwiki dialect to
HTML::WikiConverter allowing the conversion of HTML to Kwiki markup.

SYNOPSIS

Converting HTML to wiki markup is easy:

  use HTML::WikiConverter;
  my $wc = new HTML::WikiConverter( dialect => 'Kwiki' );
  print $wc->html2wiki( $html );

Or from the command line:

  % html2wiki --dialect Kwiki input.html > output.wiki

There's also a web interface if you're so inclined:

  http://diberri.dyndns.org/wikipedia/html2wiki/

CHANGES IN 0.51

  * Test suite fixed so installation should proceed normally

DEPENDENCIES

  * HTML::WikiConverter version 0.55

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc HTML::WikiConverter::Kwiki

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/HTML-WikiConverter-Kwiki

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=HTML-WikiConverter-Kwiki

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/HTML-WikiConverter-Kwiki

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/HTML-WikiConverter-Kwiki

